\end{align*}
$$

The circuit representation of (8.57) and (8.58) can be found by neglecting the feedback generator of the basic amplifier and the forward transmission generator of the feedback network in Figure 8.13a. This simplifies the circuit to the form shown in Figure 8.13b, where the terminal admittances $y_{11 f}$ and $y_{22 f}$ of the feedback network are absorbed into the basic amplifier, along with source and load admittances $y_S$ and $y_L$. This new basic amplifier incorporates the loading effect of the original feedback network, and the new feedback network is ideal as in Figure 8.9. The transfer functions of the basic amplifier and the feedback network of Figure 8.13b can be determined using these equations.

