$$
f=\frac{5}{5+20}=0.2
$$

Thus, the loop gain is

$$
T=a f=1202 \times 0.2=240
$$

The input impedance of the feedback amplifier is therefore

$$
Z_{i}=z_{i a}(1+T)=104 \times 241 \mathrm{k} \Omega=25 \mathrm{M} \Omega
$$

