Series-shunt feedback is illustrated schematically in Fig. 8.4. Both the basic amplifier and the feedback network share the same input current and output voltage. A two-port model utilizing input current and output voltage as independent variables is the hybrid $h$-parameter model, depicted in Fig. 8.22. These $h$ parameters can depict nonideal circuits in a series-shunt feedback configuration, as illustrated in Fig. 8.23a. Summing voltages at the input of this figure yields:

